{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782431220624,"sessionID":"ses_0fed24bcdffeefk85wgT09sm9w","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_55d261b7d88f4d5eb8e9279e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/private/tmp/play-comp-ws/README.md"},"output":"<path>/private/tmp/play-comp-ws/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # tinybank\n2: \n3: A minimal in-memory bank account library.\n4: \n5: ## Usage\n6: \n7: ```python\n8: from account import Account\n9: \n10: acct = Account(100)\n11: acct.deposit(50)   # 150\n12: acct.withdraw(30)  # 130\n13: ```\n14: \n15: ## API\n16: \n17: - `Account(balance=0)` - create an account.\n18: - `Account.deposit(amount)` - add to the balance.\n19: - `Account.withdraw(amount)` - subtract from the balance.\n20: - `Account.transfer(other, amount)` - move money to another account.\n21: \n22: ## Interest\n23: \n24: Use `apply_interest(balance, rate)` to apply an interest rate to a balance.\n25: For example, `apply_interest(100, 0.05)` returns `105.0`.\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# tinybank\n\nA minimal in-memory bank account library.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom account import Account\n\nacct = Account(100)\nacct.deposit(50)   # 150\nacct.withdraw(30)  # 130\n```\n\n## API\n\n- `Account(balance=0)` - create an account.\n- `Account.deposit(amount)` - add to the balance.\n- `Account.withdraw(amount)` - subtract from the balance.\n- `Account.transfer(other, amount)` - move money to another account.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/private/tmp/play-comp-ws/README.md","text":"# tinybank\n\nA minimal in-memory bank account library.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom account import Account\n\nacct = Account(100)\nacct.deposit(50)   # 150\nacct.withdraw(30)  # 130\n```\n\n## API\n\n- `Account(balance=0)` - create an account.\n- `Account.deposit(amount)` - add to the balance.\n- `Account.withdraw(amount)` - subtract from the balance.\n- `Account.transfer(other, amount)` - move money to another account.\n\n## Interest\n\nUse `apply_interest(balance, rate)` to apply an interest rate to a balance.\nFor example, `apply_interest(100, 0.05)` returns `105.0`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":25,"totalLines":25,"truncated":false}},"title":"private/tmp/play-comp-ws/README.md","time":{"start":1782431220612,"end":1782431220622}},"id":"prt_f012e0377001yL2A2fdS0veFrK","sessionID":"ses_0fed24bcdffeefk85wgT09sm9w","messageID":"msg_f012df1dd00191qWLYBbJWYBb4"}}
